race.description: Paddy Walsh Painting & Solid Plastering Mdn Hcp
race.comment: HIGHLAND KITTY (4) may have found the right race here. Has placed three of her past four outings including two around this circuit. Gets 2kg weight relief with the claim and this is not an overly strong affair. Should prove very hard to toss. NARUKAMI (3) will be better for two racetrack experiences and is another to get some weight off. Watch for sharp improvement. LOTTERY LINK (2) is drawn to get a cosy run from gate two and must be respected out of the Heathcote camp. In the mix. ALASKA DE LUNE (8) strips fitter second-up from the break and may earn some minor money. The well-related ESPOIR DA TAP (6) (half to G2 winner Tapildoodledo) best of the rest.
